<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="219" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[186,1302,215,1962]" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis box="[261,399,962,990]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species has large individuals, with typical large brownish wings, and belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[556,705,999,1027]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">nigripenne-</emphasis>
group, being recognized especially in males by the shape of sternite 7 (
<figureCitation box="[564,647,1035,1064]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
B), which has strongly developed postero-lateral projections, with prominent spiracles, and medially largely truncate posterior margin; the pointed gonocoxites (
<figureCitation box="[583,662,1110,1139]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
C) and the strongly asymmetrical posterior projection of the epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[529,608,1147,1176]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
D) are also characteristic of this species. The female has unique transversally wrinkled valvifers on sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[923,1000,1185,1214]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="220" pageId="20" pageNumber="219" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[186,1302,215,1962]" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis box="[261,420,1223,1251]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Description.</emphasis>
Male. 1.8 mm long; dull black in general colour, with pilosity lighter; a pair of light spots on notum posteriorly to wing bases; wings blackishbrown, with lighter zones between anterior stem vein on M, and apex of R4+5, at the base of wing between basal part of M and CuA2 and along vena spuria; anterior veins blackish brown, well marked, posterior veins brownish, base of wing more yellowish; halters dark, with contrasting fulvous stem; legs concolourous with body, except basal fourth or third of tibiae and tarsi lighter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[186,1302,215,1962]" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Head. Eyes separated on frons above antennae by width of anterior ocellus; antennae shorter than head and thorax together, widening apically, flagellomeres well separated, easy to count, wider than long from 4lh flagellomere on, last flagellomere about twice preceding one.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[186,1302,215,1962]" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">
Thorax quadrate, slightly wider than long; wing (
<figureCitation box="[917,998,1634,1663]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
E), 2.5 mm; no visible anteriorly directed stem of vein on M,, which has a strongly marked bend at basal iourth; M1+2 about as long as medial fork.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[186,1302,215,1962]" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">
Abdomen. Pregenital segment with a complete basal sclerotized ring; tergite 7 (
<figureCitation box="[232,316,1783,1812]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
A) with slightly asymmetrical digitiform posterior projection; sternite 7 (
<figureCitation box="[200,281,1820,1849]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
B) with strongly developed lateral projections encompassing tergite, bearing prominent spiracles; genital capsule (
<figureCitation box="[697,781,1858,1887]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
C) with pointed gonocoxites, elongate parameres, posterior process of epandrium strongly asymmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1154,1895,1924]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="219">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
D); aedeagus long, often strongly projecting.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[258,1384,200,1201]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
Female. As male in general colour and appearance; tergite 7 with posterior margin deeply notched medially (
<figureCitation box="[713,795,238,267]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
F); stemite 8 bearing a pair of transversally wrinkled elongate valvifers (
<figureCitation box="[628,704,275,304]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="17.[272,311,1764,1788]" captionTargetBox="[274,1393,222,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[273,1392,222,1412]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 6. Colobostema infumatum (Haliday): A. Tergite 7, ♂. - B. Sternite 7, ♂. - C. Génital capsule, ♂, ventral. - D. Epandrium, distal part, ♂, dorsal. - E. Wing venation, ♂. - F. Tergite 7, ♀. - G. Sternite 8, ♀ (detail), with valvifers." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270247/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[258,1384,200,1201]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis box="[337,610,313,342]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Former authors have all accepted the synonymy of C. 
<taxonomicName box="[261,380,350,379]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Scatopse" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infurnata">
<emphasis box="[261,380,350,379]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">infurnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with C. 
<emphasis box="[504,651,351,379]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<taxonomicName box="[504,646,351,379]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Colobostema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripenne">nigripenne</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
first established by Walker in 1856 (sec. Cook 1974). Although it is not possible to ensure with certainty the identity of the specimen in the Haliday collection considered here as the primary type (see O’Connor &amp; Nash 1982), there are good reasons for its designation as lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Haliday. This" authorityName="Haliday. This" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Scatopse" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infurnata">
<emphasis box="[1137,1382,462,491]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Scatopse infurnata</emphasis>
Haliday. This
</taxonomicName>
specimen fits well with the very short original description and is preserved as such in Haliday’s collection in the National Museum of Ireland in Dublin. It belongs not to C. 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[537,810,574,603]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Colobostema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripenne">
<emphasis box="[537,676,575,603]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">nigripenne</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
, but to a distinct species with very typical segment 7 and genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="220" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="21.[258,1384,200,1201]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
The specimens of C. 
<taxonomicName box="[632,751,649,678]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Scatopse" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infurnata">
<emphasis box="[632,751,649,678]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">infurnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Wales have been studied by Paul Freeman in 1989, who correctly recognized that they were not conspecific with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Colobostema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripenne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">C. nigripenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and prepared their description under the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1018,1305,723,752]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Colobostema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1018,1305,723,752]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Colobostema cornuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1322,1382,724,752]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Freeman in litt.). However, he has retired his paper before publication in order to avoid the creation of a supplementary synonym (Freeman in litt.) and so the latter name will remain only a collection name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="220" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[258,1384,200,1201]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis box="[337,502,873,902]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known presently from the British Isles (Ireland, Wales) (Laurence &amp; James 1996), Norway (Haenni &amp; Greve 1995, 2000), Switzerland (Vaucher-von Ballmoos 1997, Haenni 1998), Finland (Krivosheina 2001), Northern Russia (Krivosheina 2000, 2001), Czech Republic (Haenni &amp; Bartâk 2006). This species is probably present in the whole of Central Europe and widespread in Northern Europe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="220" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[258,1384,200,1201]" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis box="[339,452,1097,1126]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="220">Ecology.</emphasis>
Estival species with a flight period extending from beginning of June to end of August. It appears to be restricted to peat-bogs in Western and Central Europe (Wales, Switzerland and Czech Republic), where these biotopes are relic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
